23/08/2010
ATHENS, Greece -- Airplanes were prevented from departing Greek airports for over two hours early Sunday (August 22nd) due to a technical problem. 
Hundreds of passengers were stuck in planes, waiting for communication with the air traffic control network to be restored. 
Flights to Greece were not affected, local authorities said. 
(DPA, ITAR-TASS, AP - 22/08/10)
